TITLE: Composing Multiple Independent Styles with Global Selectors
DESCRIPTION: Shows how multiple independent styles can be composed together and used with global selectors. When multiple existing classes are composed, vanilla-extract creates a new identifier to ensure they can be treated as a single class.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vanilla-extract-css/vanilla-extract/blob/master/site/docs/overview/style-composition.md#2025-04-20_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// styles.css.ts

import { style, globalStyle } from '@vanilla-extract/css';

const background = style({ background: 'mintcream' });
const padding = style({ padding: 12 });

// container = 'styles_container__8uideo2'
export const container = style([background, padding]);

globalStyle(`${container} *`, {
  boxSizing: 'border-box'
});
```

