TITLE: Problematic CSS Mocking Configuration in Jest
DESCRIPTION: Example of a Jest configuration that causes issues with vanilla-extract by mocking all CSS files, including .css.ts files that should be processed by the transformer.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vanilla-extract-css/vanilla-extract/blob/master/site/docs/overview/test-environments.md#2025-04-20_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
// package.json
{
  "jest": {
    "moduleNameMapper": {
      //  Breaks .css.ts imports
      "\\.css$": "<rootDir>/styleMock.js"
    }
  }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configuring Jest for Vanilla Extract CSS Files
DESCRIPTION: Jest configuration that sets up the transformer for .css.ts files, allowing vanilla-extract styles to be processed correctly during tests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vanilla-extract-css/vanilla-extract/blob/master/site/docs/overview/test-environments.md#2025-04-20_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
// jest.config.js
{
  "transform": {
    "\\.css\\.ts$": "@vanilla-extract/jest-transform"
  }
}
```

